data.content:
Your code doesn't actually use `Thread.Abort`, `ThreadAbortException`, or `Thread.ResetAbort`. It only uses:

- `Thread.Start()` 
- `Thread.Join()` 
- `Thread.Sleep()` 

**These APIs all work identically in .NET 8** — no migration is needed.

That said, modern .NET would typically use `Task` / `Parallel.ForEach` instead of raw threads:

```csharp
public async Task RunBatchAsync(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    await Parallel.ForEachAsync(items, async (item, ct) =>
    {
        await Task.Delay(100, ct);
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    });
}
```

This is optional — your current code will compile and run correctly on .NET 8 as-is.
